 and Florian Angeletti)</li>

<li>#12642, #13536, +<a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/ocaml/issues/14184=
">#14184</a>, +<a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/ocaml/issues/14192">#141=
92</a>: in the toplevel, print shorter paths for
constructors and labels when only some modules along their path are open.
 (Gabriel Scherer, review by Florian Angeletti)</li>

<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/ocaml/issues/14196">#14196</a>, <a =
href=3D"https://github.com/ocaml/ocaml/issues/14197">#14197</a>: ocamlprof:=
 do not instrument unreachable clauses
(Gabriel Scherer, review by Nicol=C3=A1s Ojeda B=C3=A4r, report by Ali Cagl=
ayan)</li>
</ul>
</div>
</li>
