<div id=3D"outline-container-8" class=3D"outline-2">
<h2 id=3D"8">Testo 0.2.0 - test library with support for snapshots, paralle=
l runs, xfails, timeouts</h2>
<div class=3D"outline-text-2" id=3D"text-8">
<p>
Archive: <a href=3D"https://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-testo-0-2-0-test-librar=
y-with-support-for-snapshots-parallel-runs-xfails-timeouts/17242/1">https:/=
/discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-testo-0-2-0-test-library-with-support-for-snapshot=
s-parallel-runs-xfails-timeouts/17242/1</a>
</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org5a830a3" class=3D"outline-3">
<h3 id=3D"org5a830a3">Martin Jambon announced</h3>
<div class=3D"outline-text-3" id=3D"text-org5a830a3">
<p>
Testo was designed as a feature-rich testing framework that makes common ta=
sks easy and unusual ones possible. It is similar to Alcotest but supports =
more options including notably:
</p>

<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li>snapshotting: large output capture and diffing</li>
<li>test-driven development: write tests first, make them pass later (<code=
>~expected_outcome</code> option)</li>
<li>review test results without re-running them (<code>status</code> subcom=
mand)</li>
<li>fast parallel execution supporting Windows and older OCaml versions (&g=
t;=3D 4.08)</li>
<li>complete <a href=3D"https://semgrep.github.io/testo/">documentation</a>=
: <a href=3D"https://semgrep.github.io/testo/tutorial/">tutorial</a>, <a hr=
ef=3D"https://semgrep.github.io/testo/howtos/">howto guides</a>, <a href=3D=
"https://semgrep.github.io/testo/reference/testo/Testo/index.html">OCaml AP=
I reference</a></li>
<li>timeouts (new!)</li>
</ul>

<p>
We=E2=80=99ve been using Testo at <a href=3D"https://github.com/semgrep/sem=
grep">Semgrep</a> where we need the snapshotting feature to track the outpu=
t of the <code>semgrep</code> command in end-to-end tests.
</p>

<p>
<a href=3D"https://github.com/semgrep/testo/releases/tag/0.2.0">Changes sin=
ce the last release</a> include bugfixes, a few new command-line options, a=
nd support for timeouts. Install it now with
</p>

<pre class=3D"example" id=3D"org9ee24a7">
$ opam install testo
</pre>

<p>
Testo development is an open-source community effort that <a href=3D"https:=
//github.com/semgrep/testo">happens on GitHub</a>. It has been funded by Se=
mgrep, my employer and fine purveyor of application security software. We'r=
e planning for a 1.0 release once the known Windows-specific bugs are gone.=
 No major breaking changes are in sight.
</p>

<p>
For reference, the previous announcement from last year is <a href=3D"https=
://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-testo-0-1-0-a-new-testing-framework-for-ocaml/15=
624">here</a>.
</p>

<p>
Enjoy your free software!
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-9" class=3D"outline-2">
